The paper deals with a polynomial related to graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of interlace polynomials and the mention of clique-width suggest that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of graphs and polynomials also suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CO (Combinatorics). The mention of Tutte's polynomial and its multivariate generalization suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Graph Theory). Finally, the mention of polynomial time evaluation suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
